Revision history for DBIO-PostgreSQL

{{$NEXT}}
    - Initial release as standalone distribution extracted from DBIO core
    - DBIO::PostgreSQL schema component and DBIO::PostgreSQL::Storage driver
    - DBIO::PostgreSQL::SQLMaker with PostgreSQL-specific SQL generation
    - DBIO::PostgreSQL::Loader for Schema::Loader PostgreSQL introspection
    - Three-layer architecture: Database, PgSchema, and Result components
    - PostgreSQL schema (namespace) support as first-class objects
    - Enum, composite type, and range type support
    - Index support: btree, gin, gist, brin, hash — partial, expression, INCLUDE
    - Row Level Security (RLS) policy support
    - Trigger and function management
    - Introspection via pg_catalog for all supported object types
    - Test-deploy-and-compare strategy for schema upgrades
    - Migrate test suite from DBICTest to DBIO::Test
    - Remove hardcoded $VERSION from Loader, add to load test
    - Add replicated coverage to PostgreSQL driver tests
    - Comprehensive POD documentation for all 27 modules
    - Align POD with DBIO conventions (=attr, =method collectors)
    - Restore historical Loader provenance note
